# The script of the game goes in this file.

# Declare characters used by this game. The color argument colorizes the
# name of the character.

define e = Character("Markiplier")
define p = character("Phone Guy")


# The game starts here.

label start:

    # Show a background. This uses a placeholder by default, but you can
    # add a file (named either "bg room.png" or "bg room.jpg") to the
    # images directory to show it.

    scene newspaper.png 

    "Family Pizzeria look for security guard to work the Nightshift. 12AM to 6AM" 
   
    "Moniter cameras, ensure the safety of equipment and animatronic characters" 
  
    "Freddy Fazebear's Pizza is Not Responible for any injuries/dismemberment" 
    
    ":)" 

    scene newspaper.png
    with Dissolve(.5)

    pause .5

    scene fnaf office.png 

    e "if only my youtube career took off like I hoped it did." 
 
    e "If that were the case, I wouldn't have gotten this shitty job." 

    queue sound "FNaF 1 Telephone Ringtone.mp3" 

    p "Hello..? Hello, Hello?" 

    p "Uh, I wanted to record a message for you, to help you get settled down on your first night."

    e "oh god." 
    
    e "Can I just skip this?" 

    p "No you can't" 

    e "What--!" 

    e "You said this was a recorded message!" 

    p "anywho, as I've said before, this IS a recorded message. So I can't hear anything you're saying." 
    
    p "Any responses that seem related to whatever you're saying are purely coincidental. Got it?" 

    e "..." 

    p "I said got it?" 

    menu:

        "Got it.":
            jump choice1_yes

        "You Mutha--!":
            jump choice1_no

    

    

    
    e "Ehh no company is perfect. I could either deal with haunted furry robots or Karens at TjMaxx." 

    "

    # This shows a character sprite. A placeholder is used, but you can
    # replace it by adding a file named "eileen happy.png" to the images
    # directory.

    show eileen happy

    # These display lines of dialogue.

    e "You've created a new Ren'Py game."

    e "Once you add a story, pictures, and music, you can release it to the world!"

    # This ends the game.

    return
